commit.message: fix mistakenly broken range expressions
add test for morphic literals

make time literals morphic

We make a new kind of value, which is "morphic", that is, it might have more than one type. This allows time literals to dance between being date/civil and timestamp/concrete.

more cleanup of time literals

* push error messages out on format errors instead of throwing
* switch to @lloydtabb preferred syntax for week literals
* add mysteriously overlooked hour literals
add tests for literals with time zones

restrict timezones in literals to timestamp-only granularity

for now, might need to re-work the syntax if. we want this.
move granular() to the correct place
improve timestamp literal tests
make minute-resolution timestamps granular
fix timeframe for year literals
add afterAll() to close runtimes
move time tests into their own file
literals need to be stored with timestamp resolution
add a method to return runtime list for describe.each
rename file containing all time literals

move to new time literal parser

* allow sub second timestamps
* accept ISO 8601-ish times with timestamps

at this point we are parsing, but not comprehending
existing code should work, code which uses the new
syntax is not yet supported.
